{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"06d796d5-4850-4b6d-be27-cc4810d74645","content":"You can filter by class name using the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nOr more precisely by class:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nIf the class is in a namespace (e.g., `MyApp.Tests.ReportExporterTests`), you can use the fully qualified name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so it matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"41f7710a-9877-4d6a-a066-3b17b2c5fd20","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. Let me check the test files to give accurate advice.","outputTokens":209,"requestId":"1BCF:2EF340:722E498:7AB2918:6A03D547"},"id":"6fde6a71-c654-4986-9fd4-882f1e385768","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:35:09.094Z","parentId":"1ab309bf-9223-4463-ba77-d0c4d5b2ecd8"}
